  <item>
    <title>Building Community Controlled Digital Infrastructure in Detroit</title>
    <link>http://commotionwireless.net/fr/blog/building-community-controlled-digital-infrastructure-detroit</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://oti.newamerica.net/sites/newamerica.net/files/articles/images/DS_classBW.jpg&quot; width=&quot;300px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Community members launched two new wireless networks at the end of April in Detroit neighborhoods, with a third one still in the works. Built on the Commotion mesh wireless platform, these networks function as local communications infrastructure: they act as an intranet for community interactions, and connect to the global Internet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
